Early this week, I joined my colleagues in urging 
@POTUS to extend TPS to Ukrainians in the U.S., and I’m glad that he's acted on it.

The U.S. should be a safe haven for those escaping persecution and danger, including the brave Ukrainians who cannot return to their homeland. https://t.co/AithV1zOcD

Trees create cool shaded areas in cities, decrease surface temperatures, and help prevent heat related deaths.
 
@RepBonnie's SHADE Act would create a grant program under HUD to plant trees in formerly redlined districts and overburdened communities.
https://t.co/ALkFx7jvqp

One year ago today, Breonna Taylor was tragically murdered in her own home. 

We cannot allow this to happen ever again.

@HouseDemocrats passed the Justice In Policing Act this week to end police brutality, hold police accountable, and improve transparency in law enforcement.

New Jersey is on the front lines of the #ClimateCrisis, and we are leading the way on clean energy solutions. 

@GovMurphy is committed to moving New Jersey towards 100 percent clean energy by 2050.

My #CLEANFuture Act will put America on that path at the national level. https://t.co/uN8wmsSXZq

Trump's withdrawal of support for US partner forces in Syria is directly tied to Turkey's deadly attacks against civilian populations there. 

@StateDept can't let Erdogan use these attacks as an excuse to expand their brutal campaign in the region. 
https://t.co/vUft93uYh9

Since the onset of the pandemic, shortages of PPE, COVID tests &amp; supplies have hampered our efforts to crush the virus.

@POTUS has taken action to ramp up the production of supplies and to provide additional federal support at vaccination sites.

https://t.co/bX1HLYcH4P

Accident victims should be able to focus on recovery without worrying about being taken advantage of.

@EnergyCommerce will get to the bottom of this - we must protect patients against this egregious billing practice.  
https://t.co/J9E5F2z5yQ

Yesterday, @POTUS reopened the federal marketplace @HealthCareGov to help uninsured Americans during the pandemic.

@GovMurphy announced uninsured NJ residents will have until May 15th to enroll in the state marketplace as well. 

▶️Visit https://t.co/3K1H0CI435 for more info. https://t.co/bWuiYot40n

What a difference a day makes! 

@POTUS is already working hard to undo the damage of the past four years and is taking decisive action. Finally, we have a leader that is ready to work on the challenges facing our nation.
https://t.co/erQs2UksvS
